<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/5919732-carol">Carol</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I think it could work for 9th graders. The vocabulary is not too difficult. There are some mature themes in the book; however, I think 9th graders cou<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I think it could work for 9th graders. The vocabulary is not too difficult. There are some mature themes in the book; however, I think 9th graders could handle it.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
