  <span id="freeText574347490798266630" style="display:none">Swallows of Kabul is a book that shows us a city turned into dirt and ruins because of all of the continuous war. Even the people themselves have become just as ugly as the city, which once was filled with music and happiness. Children excitedly following poor stray dogs to kill them, their innocence gone. People fighting to be the first to throw stones on a woman being executed in front of them. It made me want to throw the book out the window; so much injustice, so much sadness, so much cruelty. <br /><br />It is written in a simple language and it is easy to understand. Although if someone would like to read books with this theme, I'd recommend <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/128029.A_Thousand_Splendid_Suns" title="A Thousand Splendid Suns by Khaled Hosseini" rel="nofollow noopener">A Thousand Splendid Suns</a> and <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/77203.The_Kite_Runner" title="The Kite Runner by Khaled Hosseini" rel="nofollow noopener">The Kite Runner</a>. </span>
